article.headline: Brown 80, Army 73
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Peter Sullivan scored 26 points and Chris Skrelja added 15 points and 11 assists as Brown defeated Army, 80-73, on Wednesday night. Army led 59-56 with just under six minutes remaining. But Brown went on a 16-4 run that started and ended with 3-point shots by Sullivan and gave Brown a 72-63 lead they wouldn't lose. Army closed to 76-73 on a 3-point shot by Julian Simmons with 25 seconds left. But Brown answered with a Matt Mullery layup and two Skrelja free throws. Sullivan was 9-of-15 from the field, including 5-of-9 from 3-point range. Mullery added 17 points and five blocked shots for Brown (2-3). Simmons led Army (1-4) with 18 points, while Josh Miller scored 16.
